{"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"tokens":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"matchingSemantics","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"text":"_","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"semanticLevel","kind":"internalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"identifier":"doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift/RegexSemanticLevel","text":"RegexSemanticLevel","preciseIdentifier":"s:17_StringProcessing18RegexSemanticLevelV","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":") -> ","kind":"text"},{"identifier":"doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift/Regex","preciseIdentifier":"s:17_StringProcessing5RegexV","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Regex"},{"kind":"text","text":"<"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:17_StringProcessing5RegexV0C6Outputa","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"RegexOutput"},{"kind":"text","text":">"}],"languages":["swift"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"parameters":[{"name":"semanticLevel","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The semantics to use during matching.","type":"text"}]}]}],"kind":"parameters"},{"content":[{"anchor":"return-value","type":"heading","text":"Return Value","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The modified regular expression."}]}],"kind":"content"},{"content":[{"text":"Discussion","level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"When matching with grapheme cluster semantics (the default),"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"metacharacters like "},{"code":".","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"code":"\\w","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", custom character classes, and character"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"class instances like "},{"code":".any","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" match a grapheme cluster when possible,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"corresponding with the default string representation. In addition,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"matching with grapheme cluster semantics compares characters using their"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"canonical representation, corresponding with how strings comparison works."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"When matching with Unicode scalar semantics, metacharacters and character","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"classes always match a single Unicode scalar value, even if that scalar","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"comprises part of a grapheme cluster.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"These semantic levels can lead to different results, especially when","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"working with strings that have decomposed characters. In the following"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"example, "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"queRegex"},{"type":"text","text":" matches any 3-character string that begins with "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"\"q\""},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["let composed = \"qué\"","let decomposed = \"que\\u{301}\"","","let queRegex = /^q..$/","","print(composed.contains(queRegex))","// Prints \"true\"","print(decomposed.contains(queRegex))","// Prints \"true\""]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"When using Unicode scalar semantics, however, the regular expression only","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"matches the composed version of the string, because each ","type":"text"},{"code":".","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" matches a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"single Unicode scalar value.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["let queRegexScalar = queRegex.matchingSemantics(.unicodeScalar)","print(composed.contains(queRegexScalar))","// Prints \"true\"","print(decomposed.contains(queRegexScalar))","// Prints \"false\""]}],"kind":"content"}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift","doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift/Regex"]]},"sections":[],"variants":[{"paths":["/documentation/swift/regex/matchingsemantics(_:)"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift/Regex/matchingSemantics(_:)"},"metadata":{"role":"symbol","title":"matchingSemantics(_:)","modules":[{"name":"Swift","relatedModules":[]}],"externalID":"s:17_StringProcessing5RegexV17matchingSemanticsyACyxGAA0C13SemanticLevelVF","extendedModule":"_StringProcessing","roleHeading":"Instance Method","symbolKind":"method","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"matchingSemantics"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"RegexSemanticLevel","preciseIdentifier":"s:17_StringProcessing18RegexSemanticLevelV"},{"kind":"text","text":") -> "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Regex","preciseIdentifier":"s:17_StringProcessing5RegexV"},{"kind":"text","text":"<"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"RegexOutput","preciseIdentifier":"s:17_StringProcessing5RegexV0C6Outputa"},{"kind":"text","text":">"}]},"kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"text":"Returns a regular expression that matches with the specified semantic","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"level.","type":"text"}],"references":{"doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift":{"type":"topic","title":"Swift","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Build apps using a powerful open language."}],"kind":"symbol","url":"/documentation/swift","role":"collection","identifier":"doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift"},"doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift/RegexSemanticLevel":{"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"RegexSemanticLevel"}],"abstract